The accident happened on Hammerfest Road on Monday afternoon when a taxi collided with a light motor vehicle. JOHANNESBURG - Sixteen children have been injured in a taxi accident in Centurion, Gauteng.The accident happened on Hammerfest Road on Monday afternoon when a taxi collided with a light motor vehicle.ER24's Russel Meiring says when paramedics arrived on the scene, the children were on the pavement.Meiring says 13 patients have been taken to hospital for further treatment. We immediately assessed the patients and found that a total of 16 had sustained minor to moderate injuries. Fortunately, no serious or fatal injuries were reported. The patients were treated for their injuries and later transported 13 of them to various hospitals in the area for further treatment. 